shared-library patch acl100413 (version 313) ...
Date Posted: Thu Aug  4 15:47:41 PDT 2016
Patch names: acl100413 (version 313), acli100413, libacl100413,
  libacli100413, libacl100413s, libacli100413s, acl100413s,
  acli100413s, libacl100416, libacli100416, acl100416, acli100416,
  libacl100416s, libacli100416s, acl100416s, acli100416s,
  acli10041t3, libacli10041t3
Description: Some types of foreign calls were not fully initializing
  a control block on the stack, and this could make the garbage
  collector find an invalid pointer where it expected a valid one.
  The garbage collector would generally react to this by displaying a
  fatal error message and terminating the process.
Impact: recommended

