compiler patch pkb002
Date Posted: Fri Dec 11 10:13:29 PST 2015
Patch names: update/pkb002.001
Description: Fixes a regression in the compilaton of any macros which
  make restarts; these forms cause some closures not to be
  stack-allocated that were in 9.0. This patch brings back the
  stack-allocation, and thus improves performance both at run-time
  and gc time.
Impact: recommended
Other info: Since this patch is compiler-related, any affected code
  must be recompiled after the patch is installed.

